David I just read an article put out by reflex media  (
www.reflex-media.net
) in a what looks like insert of a news paper in the Netherlands.  They are talking about the promising results in a study by an immunologist Dr. Bart Roep of the Leiden University where they take 2 dl (200cc, 7 fl.oz.) of your own blood and infuse/work on the immune cells with Vitamin D3 and a anti-bio-tic.  After this is done the blood is re-introduced in your body and based on how many beta cells you still have it will start to generate more and stronger beta cells keeping the immune system at bay.  This is again as stated B-4 great for newly discovered and young diabetics but won't work for people with 40 plus years of Type 1 and no more Beta cells.

